The paper deals with handwriting recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of dropout as a regularization method suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with the modeling of sequences, which suggests that it could belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks suggests that the paper could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
